					<h4>Eleni</h4>
					<p>
						Team One’s ideal jobs span the gamut of the IT landscape.<br>
						We have two software developers: Chris focusing on web application development and myself as a
						cloud software developer.
						These represent some of the most in demand occupations and skill sets according to Burning
						Glass.<br><br>
						John’s ideal role as senior systems administrator represents another in demand job and an
						expansion into management, planning and analysis.<br><br>
						Romaisa’s role as an IT Trainer requires the top baseline skills. These include: communication
						skills, writing, planning, and teamwork.
						The success of this role lies in highly developed IT soft skills.<br><br>
						Ben’s role as a cyber security analyst is another role, along with John and Romaisa, requires
						analytical, planning and communication skills,
						in addition to specific IT skills in networking, system administration and software testing.<br><br>
						All roles require proficient soft skills such as problem solving, teamwork and communication
						skills. Soft skills are an integral part of any IT role today (Doyle 2019).
						The specific IT skills vary depending on the role, as they each have highly specific
						requirements.
